    "bullets": [
      "Cross-national survey evidence on AI trust and adoption drawn from Gillespie et al. 2025, covering 48,340 respondents across 47 countries, framed as a conceptual study of AI paradigm generations.",
      "No language model is used as a research instrument; ChatGPT is treated as the object of study, with adoption and trust modeled through an n-ball volume recursion.",
      "Reports 66 percent regular AI usage alongside only 46 percent trusting AI, with trust falling from 63 to 56 percent between 2022 and 2025 as adoption doubled."
    ],
